headline: Centene (CNC): Assessing Valuation After a 10% 1-Month and 29% 3-Month Share Price Rebound
summary: Centene (CNC) has quietly climbed about 10% over the past month and nearly 29% in the past 3 months, even as its 1 year return remains deeply negative. This sets up an interesting reset story. See our latest analysis for Centene. The 1 month share price return of 9.7% and 3 month share price gain of roughly 29% suggest momentum is rebuilding, even as the 1 year total shareholder return remains sharply negative and longer term holders are still under water.
